  "name": "The Hadal Zone",
  "mood": "Submerged",
  "engines": [
    "Obrix"
  ],
  "description": "The deepest location in this entire collection. distance=0.95 — maximum HF rolloff, maximum depth. Only two points deeper exist in the ocean: the Challenger Deep, and silence. Sine src1 against Sine src2 one octave below, minimal FM (0.12) for the slight pressure-warping of pure tone. proc1=LP at 90 Hz removes almost everything. Journey Mode is obligatory — there is no note-off at this depth, only continuation. Four mods work in geological time: LFO->Volume at 0.004 Hz (barely perceptible, barely alive), Env->FilterCutoff (opens 40 Hz peak then closes), Velocity->FilterCutoff (pressure sensitivity), Aftertouch->Volume (you lean into the dark). brightness=0.03 is near-total darkness.",
